<!--
    Turkish (tr) — translated from values-de/ (German source of truth).

    Script notes:
    • Latin alphabet with Turkish-specific characters: ç, ğ, ı (dotless i),
      İ (dotted I), ö, ş, ü. These are all standard Unicode and render
      correctly on Android without extra font configuration.
    • IMPORTANT — Turkish i/İ dotting rule: the uppercase of "i" is "İ"
      (dotted), not "I". Android's Locale-aware toUpperCase() handles this
      correctly for locale tr; no manual workaround needed in string resources.
    • Register: polite second-person singular (siz-form) as is standard for
      Turkish app UIs.
    • "Binge drinking" → aşırı içki içme (public-health term in Turkish).
    • DHS is kept as "DHS" (Deutsche Hauptstelle für Suchtfragen); WHO as "WHO".
    • day_change_time_value: Turkish clock notation uses no suffix for 24-hour
      format; HH:MM is used as-is (same as the format string).
    • Decimal separator in Turkish is a comma (,), but numeric format strings
      are pre-formatted by the app, so no change needed in string resources.
-->
